2.4.4 Using "in" to check collection and range membership
	- use "in" operator to check whether a value is in a range <-> opposite is "!in"
		ex)
			======================================================
			fun isLetter(c: Char) = c in 'a'..'z' || c in 'A'..'Z'
			fun isNotDigit(c: Char) = c !in '0'..'9'
			======================================================

	- you can also use in when expressions
		ex)
			======================================================
			when(c){
				in '0'..'9' -> "digit"
				in 'a'..'z' -> "alphabet"
				else -> "i don't know"
			}
			======================================================
	
	- also use with collections
		ex) set example
			======================================================
			println("Kotlin" in setOf("Java", "Scala"))
			======================================================
	

